This paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) category as it deals with the detection and characterization of phishing attacks, which is a major concern in the field of cybersecurity. The paper also uses machine learning techniques to develop a classifier, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the thematic content and recipient targeting strategies used by attackers, which could fall under the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) category. Finally, the paper also touches upon the estimation of success rates of attacks, which could be relevant to the cs.CY (Computers and Society) category.
